        "content": "**What does this symbol mean? Do some research.**\n![[UL-listed.png|150]]\n**What does this symbol mean? Do some research.**\n![[CE Mark.png|150]]\n**What does this symbol mean? Do some research.**\n![[RTM Mark.png|150]]\n\n#### Read this OpEd from 2023.\n<iframe src=\"https://carnegieendowment.org/posts/2023/07/its-time-to-create-a-national-registry-for-large-ai-models?lang=en\" width=\"100%\" height=\"500\"></iframe>\nWhat is the main purpose of the authors' proposed AI registration system?\n(>)To give governments basic visibility into who is developing large generative AI models and their potential risks.\nTo make all AI development data publicly available to promote transparency.\nTo restrict the public’s access to AI technologies like ChatGPT.\nTo slow down innovation until new international laws are passed.\n\n_The author argues that governments currently lack visibility into who is building powerful AI models and what those models can do. Registration would provide basic information to enable oversight and informed policymaking._\n\n**See if Wilber, J. 2024 can explain \"[What Exactly Is ISO Certified? And Why Does It Matter?](https://www.meadmetals.com/blog/what-exactly-is-iso-certified-and-what-does-it-mean)\"**\n\n**If your are still not sure: [ask GOOGLE](https://www.google.com/search?q=what+is+iso+certification&oq=what+is+iso+certification)! Or, watch **\n![this video](https://youtu.be/a4cyMAIyWIQ?si=qZhGCD0mnngl7yGI):\n\n\n**Read [this AI Synopsis of an excerpt from Michel Foucault's _Discipline and Punish_](https://jhu.instructure.com/courses/104047/pages/foucault-the-means-of-correct-training-ai-synopsis \"Foucault \\\"The Means of Correct Training\\\" [AI Synopsis]\").** Full text optional below.\n\n- [Foucault \"The Means of Correct Training\" [AI Synopsis]](https://jhu.instructure.com/courses/104047/pages/foucault-the-means-of-correct-training-ai-synopsis \"Foucault \\\"The Means of Correct Training\\\" [AI Synopsis]\")\n- OPTIONAL: [Foucault M The Means of Correct Training.pdf](https://jhu.instructure.com/courses/104047/files/14916503?wrap=1 \"Link\") \n    \n    [](https://jhu.instructure.com/courses/104047/quizzes/266398/edit#)  (full text)\n\n**According to Foucault in _“The Means of Correct Training,”_ how does modern disciplinary power produce “qualified” individuals?**\n\n\nTake a look at the alignment cards I have in the category \"QUALIFICATION.\"\n\n<iframe src=\"https://innoeduvation.org/danryan/production/teaching/hmia/alignmentCards/original/index.html?category=Q\" width=\"100%\" height=\"600\"></iframe>"
